<subSubSection lastPageId="126" lastPageNumber="126" pageId="125" pageNumber="125" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="125.[704,1234,1124,1763]" lastBlockId="126.[94,623,845,1572]" lastPageId="126" lastPageNumber="126" pageId="125" pageNumber="125">
IDENTIFICATION: The principal reference on bats of the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[914,1035,1417,1440]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Uroderma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="125" pageNumber="125" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[914,1035,1417,1440]" italics="true" pageId="125" pageNumber="125">Uroderma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is Davis (1968), who described the species in detail and provided figures and measurements. Helpful descriptions and comparative measurments of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1866" box="[704,860,1534,1558]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Uroderma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="125" pageNumber="125" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bilobatum">
<emphasis box="[704,725,1535,1558]" italics="true" pageId="125" pageNumber="125">U</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[742,860,1535,1558]" italics="true" pageId="125" pageNumber="125">bilobatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can also be found in 
<bibRefCitation author="Goodwin, G. G. &amp; A. M. Greenhall" journalOrPublisher="Bull. Am. Mus. Nat. Hist." pageId="125" pageNumber="125" pagination="191 - 301" part="122" refId="ref94360" refString="Goodwin, G. G., and A. M. Greenhall 1961. A review of the bats of Trinidad and Tobago: descriptions, rabies infection, and ecology. Bull. Am. Mus. Nat. Hist. 122: 191 - 301." title="A review of the bats of Trinidad and Tobago: descriptions, rabies infection, and ecology" type="journal article" year="1961">Goodwin and Greenhall (1961)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Husson, A. M." bookContentInfo="282 pp." box="[975,1143,1564,1587]" journalOrPublisher="Zool. Verh. Rijksmus. Nat. Hist. (Leiden) 52" pageId="125" pageNumber="125" refId="ref95767" refString="Husson, A. M. 1962. The bats of Suriname. Zool. Verh. Rijksmus. Nat. Hist. (Leiden) 52: 282 pp. 1 30 pls." title="The bats of Suriname" type="book" year="1962">Husson (1962</bibRefCitation>
, 1978), Swanepoel and 
<bibRefCitation author="Genoways, H. H. &amp; S. L. Williams" box="[890,1101,1593,1616]" journalOrPublisher="Ann. Carnegie Mus." pageId="125" pageNumber="125" pagination="323 - 335" part="48" refId="ref93773" refString="Genoways, H. H., and S. L. Williams 1979. Records of bats (Mammalia: Chiroptera) from Suriname. Ann. Carnegie Mus. 48: 323 - 335." title="Records of bats (Mammalia: Chiroptera) from Suriname" type="journal article" year="1979">Genoways (1979)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Baker, R. J. &amp; C. L. Clark" bookContentInfo="4 pp." journalOrPublisher="Mamm. Species 279" pageId="125" pageNumber="125" refId="ref91345" refString="Baker, R. J., and C. L. Clark 1987. Uroderma bilobatum. Mamm. Species 279: 4 pp." title="Uroderma bilobatum" type="book" year="1987">Baker and Clark (1987)</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Brosset, A. &amp; P. Charles-Dominique" journalOrPublisher="Mammalia" pageId="125" pageNumber="125" pagination="509 - 559" part="54" refId="ref91807" refString="Brosset, A., and P. Charles-Dominique 1990. The bats from French Guiana: a taxonomic, faunistic and ecological approach. Mammalia 54: 509 - 559." title="The bats from French Guiana: a taxonomic, faunistic and ecological approach" type="journal article" year="1990">Brosset and CharlesÂ­Dominique (1990)</bibRefCitation>
. Six subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1866" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Uroderma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="125" pageNumber="125" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bilobatum">
<emphasis box="[1108,1129,1652,1675]" italics="true" pageId="125" pageNumber="125">U</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="125" pageNumber="125">bilobatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are currently recognized, of which the nominate 
<taxonomicName box="[821,962,1710,1733]" form="occurs" pageId="125" pageNumber="125" rank="form">form occurs</taxonomicName>
throughout Amazonia, including the Guianas (Davis, 1968; 
<bibRefCitation author="Baker, R. J. &amp; W. R. Atchley &amp; V. R. McDaniel" journalOrPublisher="Syst. Zool." lastPageId="126" lastPageNumber="126" pageId="125" pageNumber="125" pagination="414 - 429" part="21" refId="ref91297" refString="Baker, R. J., W. R. Atchley, and V. R. McDaniel 1972. Karyology and morphometrics of Peters' tent-making bat, Uroderma bilobatum Peters (Chiroptera, Phyllostomatidae). Syst. Zool. 21: 414 - 429." title="Karyology and morphometrics of Peters' tent-making bat, Uroderma bilobatum Peters (Chiroptera, Phyllostomatidae)" type="journal article" year="1972">Baker et al., 1972</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Baker, R. J. &amp; C. L. Clark" bookContentInfo="4 pp." box="[214,487,845,868]" journalOrPublisher="Mamm. Species 279" pageId="126" pageNumber="126" refId="ref91345" refString="Baker, R. J., and C. L. Clark 1987. Uroderma bilobatum. Mamm. Species 279: 4 pp." title="Uroderma bilobatum" type="book" year="1987">Baker and Clark, 1987</bibRefCitation>
; Koopman, 1994).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="126.[94,623,845,1572]" pageId="126" pageNumber="126">
Our voucher material conforms in all respects with published descriptions of this species, and our measurement data fall within the range of variation previously reported for 
<emphasis box="[137,158,1021,1044]" italics="true" pageId="126" pageNumber="126">U</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[176,191,1021,1044]" italics="true" pageId="126" pageNumber="126">b</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1866" box="[208,326,1021,1044]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Uroderma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="126" pageNumber="126" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bilobatum">
<emphasis box="[208,326,1021,1044]" italics="true" pageId="126" pageNumber="126">bilobatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="126" pageNumber="126" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="126.[94,623,845,1572]" pageId="126" pageNumber="126">
FIELD OBSERVATIONS: We captured 25 individuals of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1866" box="[239,486,1080,1103]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Uroderma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="126" pageNumber="126" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bilobatum">
<emphasis box="[239,486,1080,1103]" italics="true" pageId="126" pageNumber="126">Uroderma bilobatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at Paracou, of which 21 were taken in groundÂ­level mistnets and 4 at roosts. Of the 21 groundÂ­level mistnet captures, 6 were in swampy primary forest, 5 were in creekside primary forest, 6 were in manmade clearings, and 4 were over roadside puddles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="126.[94,623,845,1572]" pageId="126" pageNumber="126">
We found two roosting groups, each in an ââapicalââ tent (sensu 
<bibRefCitation author="Kunz, T. H. &amp; M. S. Fujita &amp; A. P. Brooke &amp; G. F. McCracken" box="[340,543,1314,1337]" journalOrPublisher="J. Mammal. Evol." pageId="126" pageNumber="126" pagination="57 - 78" part="2" refId="ref96742" refString="Kunz, T. H., M. S. Fujita, A. P. Brooke, and G. F. McCracken 1994. Convergence in tent architecture and tent-making behavior among Neotropical and Paleotropical bats. J. Mammal. Evol. 2: 57 - 78." title="Convergence in tent architecture and tent-making behavior among Neotropical and Paleotropical bats" type="journal article" year="1994">Kunz et al., 1994</bibRefCitation>
) made by chewing through the midrib of a large leaf of 
<taxonomicName box="[130,487,1373,1396]" class="Liliopsida" family="Strelitziaceae" genus="Phenakospermum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zingiberales" pageId="126" pageNumber="126" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="guyannense">
<emphasis box="[130,487,1373,1396]" italics="true" pageId="126" pageNumber="126">Phenakospermum guyannense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Strelitziaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zingiberales" pageId="126" pageNumber="126" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Strelitziaceae</taxonomicName>
) (fig. 51). A roosting group of three bats collected in its entirety consisted of an adult male, a lactating adult female, and a juvenile. Both roosts were in swampy primary forest; one tent was 3.5 m and the other 5 m above the ground.
</paragraph>
